helpdesk-ticket.subject: Updates for Library Proxy Server Config File
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hi Support, The library EZproxy server config.txt file needs to be updated. After the file is updated, the EZproxy server software needs to be re-started for the changes to take effect. Here are the changes: [1] Delete the following stanza from the current config.txt file: T ScienceDirect College Edition U http://www.sciencedirect.com/ DJ sciencedirect.com ## http://www.sciencedirect.com/ [2] Insert the following stanza: # Elsevier ScienceDirect Cookie BROWSER_SUPPORTS_COOKIES=1; domain=.sciencedirect.com AnonymousURL +http://rss.sciencedirect.com/* Title SciVerse ScienceDirect URL http://www.sciencedirect.com/ HJ sciencedirect.com DJ sciencedirect.com HJ linkinghub.elsevier.com DJ *.els-cdn.com Find value="http:// Replace value="http://^A Find %22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fsciverse-shindig.elsevier.com%2F Replace %22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2F^psciverse-shindig.elsevier.com^%2F Find gsUrl%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2F Replace gsUrl%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2F^pwww.sciencedirect.com^%2F Find pdfurl%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2F Replace pdfurl%3D%22http%3A%2F%2F^pwww.sciencedirect.com^%2F Option Cookie [3] After completing [1] and [2], please re-start the EZproxy. Please let me know when the tasks have been completed. If you have questions, please let me know. Thanks very much! Gary Shimek -- Director of the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hi Support,

The library EZproxy server config.txt file needs to be updated.  After the file is updated, the EZproxy server software needs to be re-started for the changes to take effect.  Here are the changes:

[1]  Delete the following stanza from the current config.txt file:

T ScienceDirect College Edition
U http://www.sciencedirect.com/
DJ sciencedirect.com
## http://www.sciencedirect.com/

[2]  Insert the following stanza:
# Elsevier ScienceDirect
Cookie BROWSER_SUPPORTS_COOKIES=1; domain=.sciencedirect.com
AnonymousURL +http://rss.sciencedirect.com/*
Title SciVerse ScienceDirect
URL http://www.sciencedirect.com/
HJ sciencedirect.com
DJ sciencedirect.com
HJ linkinghub.elsevier.com
DJ *.els-cdn.com
Find value="http://
Replace value="http://^A
Find %22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fsciverse-shindig.elsevier.com%2F
Replace %22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2F^psciverse-shindig.elsevier.com^%2F
Find gsUrl%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2F
Replace gsUrl%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2F^pwww.sciencedirect.com^%2F
Find pdfurl%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2F
Replace pdfurl%3D%22http%3A%2F%2F^pwww.sciencedirect.com^%2F
Option Cookie
[3] After completing [1] and [2], please re-start the EZproxy.  Please let me know when the tasks have been completed.
If you have questions, please let me know.
Thanks very much!
Gary Shimek -- Director of the Library

helpdesk-note.body:
Kevin,
Just to clear a few things up:
Your email is kevin.blank@alumni.msoe.edu
You successfully reset this password last month.
When you put kevin.blank@alumni.msoe.edu into Google's sign on it will bring you to our SSO.
This is where you are failing to log in. There is nothing on the MSOE side causing this issue. Possible causes:
Your browser is remembering previous, bad or old credentials. Try logging in with another browser.
If this fixes your issue, you need to delete saved credentials in your current browser. Feel free to ask us for help deleting old credentials. We will be happy to send you a guide on how to do that. Even if this does not solve your issue, you probably should delete old credentials that are saved in your browser to prevent future issues.
The password that you are typing in is wrong, try resetting your password again to a known value. Try logging in to kevin.blank@alumni.msoe.edu with your new password in a different browser. Let us know if either of these fix your issue.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body: O.K., thanks for clarifying that I need to have all software-related invoices sent directly to MSOE Accounts Payable. This is actually a change in procedure. In approximately 2010, all department heads were informed that IT would assume responsibility for processing payment of software-related invoices. I believe the idea was to centralize purchasing in order to eliminate unnecessary duplicate purchases. I was informed at that time that I should no longer budget for software purchases; instead, payment would be charged to the IT budget. I was told simply to forward software-related invoices to IT, who would then process payment. The change in procedure now should probably be communicated; it would also help to be aware of whether or not annual software renewals need to be itemized in respective department budgets or whether they will continue to be paid from the IT budget. Thanks. --Gary, Library
helpdesk-note.body-html: O.K., thanks for clarifying that I need to have all software-related invoices sent directly to MSOE Accounts Payable. This is actually a change in procedure. In approximately 2010, all department heads were informed that IT would assume responsibility for processing payment of software-related invoices. I believe the idea was to centralize purchasing in order to eliminate unnecessary duplicate purchases. I was informed at that time that I should no longer budget for software purchases; instead, payment would be charged to the IT budget. I was told simply to forward software-related invoices to IT, who would then process payment. The change in procedure now should probably be communicated; it would also help to be aware of whether or not annual software renewals need to be itemized in respective department budgets or whether they will continue to be paid from the IT budget. Thanks. —Gary, Library

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Gary Shimek,
I should probably clarify. Invoices should go to AP, but quotes and yearly estimates should come to IT so we can create purchase orders for them, and make sure they are budgeted. Since the invoice needs to get paid, that has to go to AP, but if IT does not have a quote on file, we also will not have a PO req on file.
So please work with us in IT to make sure we know what software you will need, and that we have accurate quotes to create a budget, but invoices for payment should always go to AP. I'm assuming that the process has not changed, but I am certain IT does not want to be responsible for making sure an invoice is paid, just that there is money in the budget to allow it to be paid.
Thanks,
FABIAN

Dear MSOE Faculty and Staff,
In this ongoing series, Andy Holmes, Instructional Technologist, under the production of Ben Harris, Director of Desktop Management, will be delivering technology tips and best practices. This is an effort to drive high levels of performance and to ensure that the staff and faculty have what they need for daily success!
This week, student Technician, Sam West, interviews a student about password changes. The helpdesk is happy to assist. Stop in to the helpdesk in Campus Central, call x7288, email helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>, or create a ticket from theMSOE Community<https://community.msoe.edu/news> site.
This week's top story is how to create a test in Blackboard. Many instructors have been asking for the instructions listed below. Click the video link below for a brief screencast tutorial by Andy Holmes.
[cid:image002.jpg@01D19702.F677F340]<https://msoe.box.com/s/whydpy0vsy9lgltyqgm84biloxm0ls9t>
How to Import a Test
1. On the Control Panel, expand the Course Tools section and click Tests, Surveys, and Pools. 2. On the Tests, Surveys, and Pools page, click Tests. 3. Click Import on the action bar. 4. On the Import page, locate the file. Click Browse My Computer to upload a file from your computer. 5. Click Submit.
Access the Test or Survey Canvas from the Course Tools section.
On the Test or Survey Canvas, you can:
* Edit the name and instructions before students submit attempts. Access the title's contextual menu and click Edit. * Change question settings<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/080_Question_Settings>, such as setting the default point value for test questions and options for scoring. Survey questions are not graded, and student responses are anonymous. * Create questions<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/010_Create_Tests_and_Surveys#build_tests>. * Edit, reorder<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/010_Create_Tests_and_Surveys#reorder_questions>, and delete questions<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/030_Edit_Tests_and_Questions#delete_test_questions>. * Select any or all questions and change point values<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/030_Edit_Tests_and_Questions#change_point_values>. For tests, you can also change the point values of existing questions even after students submit attempts. Any submissions affected by test changes are regraded. * Reuse<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/120_Reuse_Questions> and find questions. * Add question sets<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/120_Reuse_Questions/020_Question_Sets> and random blocks<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/120_Reuse_Questions/010_Random_Block>. * Upload questions<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/120_Reuse_Questions/040_Upload_Questions>.
How to Add a Test or Survey to a Content Area
1. Navigate to the course area where you want to add a test or survey. 2. On the action bar, point to Assessments and click Test or Survey. 3. Select a test or survey from the Add Test or Add Survey list. 4. Click Submit. The Test or Survey Options page<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/020_Test_and_Survey_Options> appears.
How to Make a Test or Survey Available
After you deploy a test or survey in a course area, you set its availability.
1. On the Test Options or Survey Options page, click Yes to Make the Link Available to users. 2. Set the availability, feedback, and presentation options<https://en-us.help.blackboard.com/Learn/9.1_2014_04/Instructor/110_Tests_Surveys_Pools/020_Test_and_Survey_Options#edit_test_availability> for a test or survey, including password. 3. Click Submit.
Respectfully,
Benjamin Harris
Milwaukee School Of Engineering (MSOE)
Director of Desktop Management

Dear MSOE Faculty and Staff,
 
In this ongoing series, Andy Holmes, Instructional Technologist, under the production of Ben Harris, Director of Desktop Management, will be delivering technology tips and best practices. This is an effort to drive high levels of performance and to ensure that the staff and faculty have what they need for daily success!
 
This week, student Technician, Sam West, interviews a student about password changes.  The helpdesk is happy to assist.  Stop in to the helpdesk in Campus Central, call x7288, email helpdesk@msoe.edu, or create a ticket from theMSOE Community site.
 
This week's top story is how to create a test in Blackboard.  Many instructors have been asking for the instructions listed below.  Click the video link below for a brief screencast tutorial by Andy Holmes.
 
 
How to Import a Test
  1. On the Control Panel, expand the Course Tools section and click Tests, Surveys, and Pools.
  2. On the Tests, Surveys, and Pools page, click Tests.
  3. Click Import on the action bar.
  4. On the Import page, locate the file. Click Browse My Computer to upload a file from your computer.
  5. Click Submit.
Access the Test or Survey Canvas from the Course Tools section.
 
On the Test or Survey Canvas, you can:
  • Edit the name and instructions before students submit attempts. Access the title's contextual menu and click Edit.
  • Change question settings, such as setting the default point value for test questions and options for scoring. Survey questions are not graded, and student responses are anonymous.
  • Create questions. 
  • Edit, reorder, and delete questions.
  • Select any or all questions and change point values. For tests, you can also change the point values of existing questions even after students submit attempts. Any submissions affected by test changes are regraded.
  • Reuse and find questions.
  • Add question sets and random blocks.
  • Upload questions.
How to Add a Test or Survey to a Content Area
  1. Navigate to the course area where you want to add a test or survey.
  2. On the action bar, point to Assessments and click Test or Survey. 
  3. Select a test or survey from the Add Test or Add Survey list.
  4. Click Submit. The Test or Survey Options page appears.
How to Make a Test or Survey Available
 After you deploy a test or survey in a course area, you set its availability.
  1. On the Test Options or Survey Options page, click Yes to Make the Link Available to users.
  2. Set the availability, feedback, and presentation options for a test or survey, including password.
  3. Click Submit.
 
Respectfully,

MS Visio and MS Project are not standard to MS Office. They are only available via DreamSpark Premium. Currently, only a few departments are paying for DreamSpark Premium subscriptions. If you are a student of one of these departments, you are already enrolled in DreamSpark and should check you email history for an introductory email with instructions on how to log on and download software. The departments with active DreamSpark Premium accounts are: EECS, CAECM, and RSOB. If you are not a student of these departments, or are staff, the programs are not currently available with the MSOE license through Microsoft.
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7270 My job at FPI has made it necessary for me to use Visio but when I tried to download it from the network it told me I do not have access to the program.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi liy, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7277
Hi Yu
I'm sorry to hear that your laptop is running slowly. Feel free to uninstall anything that you feel you don't need on the machine. We don't usually have any of the core engineering software on the nursing laptops, but there may still be some stuff that you don't use, such as labview. Another option is to bring on computer into the helpdesk on CC 3rd floor and have us assist you in finding out what specifically is making the machine run slower than it should. If you need any help feel free to ask. Have a great weekend.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Tier 2 Staff Support Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

Hi liy,
Sometimes, computers running unusually slow can be due to hard drives beginning to wear out. I would suggest you bring your laptop to the desk so we can test the hard drive and make sure this isn't the case. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Michael Gans,
This should help you:
The saved outlook password needs to be updated with the current password. One way to do it is to delete the outlook password that the windows previously saved on your laptop. Once it is deleted, when you reopen the outlook, it should ask for password where in you enter the current password.
Follow the steps below in order to deleted the stored old outlook password.
Click the Start button and type-in "Credential Manager". A dialogue box should appear. In the dialogue box, under "Generic Credentials", click the vault that contains the outlook credentials. Click Remove from vault. Hit 'yes' when it asks for the confirmation to delete those credentials. Reopen Outlook. Now you should get a pop-up window asking you to enter your credentials.
Once you enter your current password, your Outlook should get connected to Microsoft Exchange and your inbox should get updated with recent emails.
Please let us know if there is anything more we can do for you. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7288

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Michael Gans,

This should help you:

The saved outlook password needs to be updated with the current password. One way to do it is to delete the outlook password that the windows previously saved on your laptop. Once it is deleted, when you reopen the outlook, it should ask for password where in you enter the current password. 
 
Follow the steps below in order to deleted the stored old outlook password. 
  1. Click the Start button  and type-in "Credential Manager". A dialogue box should appear.
  2. In the dialogue box, under "Generic Credentials", click the vault that contains the outlook credentials.
  3. Click Remove from vault.
  4. Hit 'yes' when it asks for the confirmation to delete those credentials.
  5. Reopen Outlook. Now you should get a pop-up window asking you to enter your credentials.
Once you enter your current password, your Outlook should get connected to Microsoft Exchange and your inbox should get updated with recent emails.

Please let us know if there is anything more we can do for you.

helpdesk-note.body:
Mike,
Can you clarify what your issue is? You first mentioned problems with your phone and Outlook being able to send messages. Now you are mentioning Office 365.
To be clear, MSOE does not support your personal versions of Outlook and Office365. Feel free to contact Microsoft support with regards to Outlook not working.
In an effort to help you, I took the liberty of Googling how to set up a gmail account on Outlook.
If I were you, I would try deleting and recreating my Mail account within Outlook. For Windows 7, go to Start Menu(windows key)->Control Panel->Mail->Show Profiles->delete the profile you are having problems with.
As for your android problems, I've heard of people needing to completely uninstall / reinstall the outlook app in order to get their account to work after a password change. Your personal Android Outlook app is also not supported by MSOE.
I am going to mark this ticket as resolved unless there is something MSOE related that you need help with or you provide more information about your problem.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Mike,

Can you clarify what your issue is? You first mentioned problems with your phone and Outlook being able to send messages. Now you are mentioning Office 365. 

To be clear, MSOE does not support your personal versions of Outlook and Office365. Feel free to contact Microsoft support with regards to Outlook not working. 

In an effort to help you, I took the liberty of Googling how to set up a gmail account on Outlook.

If I were you, I would try deleting and recreating my Mail account within Outlook. For Windows 7, go to Start Menu(windows key)->Control Panel->Mail->Show Profiles->delete the profile you are having problems with. 

As for your android problems, I've heard of people needing to completely uninstall / reinstall the outlook app in order to get their account to work after a password change. Your personal Android Outlook app is also not supported by MSOE. 

I am going to mark this ticket as resolved unless there is something MSOE related that you need help with or you provide more information about your problem.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Unable to connect to Chrome
helpdesk-ticket.description: Kevin came in to the desk and showed that his browser traffic may have been being controlled by a proxy. We ran ComboFix and MalwareBytes, restarted, and it seemed to resolve the issue. I recommended uninstalling any non-mainstream third party applications if the problem arises again in the future.

Are you talking about your outlook?
If that is the case, you can click Start; type in Credential Manager and click on it. Once you are at that screen, remove anything from the vault that has your msoe email in it. Once the passwords are removed, close and reopen outlook and it should prompt you to enter your new password.

Mary
Mary Nielsen Registrar Milwaukee School of Engineering Phone: 414-277-7216 Fax: 414-277-6914 www.msoe.edu
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

I am trying to change an academic advisor on the Student Division Master Screen in Student Information and I get an error.  I cannot save any information because of the error.

www.msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
From Jenzabar:
Hello Beth. The end user is receiving the error message because the ‘Transfer-in first-time in this institution’ radio button is selected AND they have not entered in the Transfer-in Year/Term.
Whenever the ‘First time in postsecondary institution’ OR the ‘Transfer-in first-time in this institution’ radio button is selected a Year/Term has to be entered for the ‘Entering First-time, Transfer in Year/Term’.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
From Jenzabar:

Hello Beth.
The end user is receiving the error message because the ‘Transfer-in first-time in this institution’ radio button is selected AND they have not entered in the Transfer-in Year/Term.
 
Whenever the ‘First time in postsecondary institution’ OR the ‘Transfer-in first-time in this institution’ radio button is selected a Year/Term has to be entered for the ‘Entering First-time, Transfer in Year/Term’.

On Mon, Apr 18, 2016 at 10:28 AM, Milwaukee School of Engineering <helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>> wrote: Your MSOE alumni account password will expire on April 30th. [MSOE Logo] [Milwaukee School of Engineering] <http://www.msoe.edu> Hello Dennis Lohr,
In an effort to make password resets easier and more secure over the next few weeks you will be required to reset your password.
Please follow the link below and reset your alumni password. The only requirement for the new password is that it is at least 8 characters long. You can even set it to the password you currently use, as long as its 8 characters long. You will also be asked for an alternate email address; it is optional to provide it but once we get the self-service password reset portal setup you will be able to use that alternate email address to reset your password.
https://gapps.msoe.edu/alumni/update_password.php
If you do not remember your password you can reset it at the following link. You do not need to complete another password change at the previous link after resetting your password.
https://gapps.msoe.edu/alumni/password/
The deadline to reset your password is April 30th. If you haven’t changed your password by April 30th you will need to contact the helpdesk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/> for assistance in resetting your password.
Getting everyone’s password reset is phase 1 of this project. Phase 2 will be getting our new self-service password reset portal setup. The new self-service password reset portal will allow you to setup security questions or use an alternate email to reset your password.
If you have any questions please contact the helpdesk at (414) 277-7288<tel:%28414%29%20277-7288> or by email at helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>. Otherwise please reset your password as soon as possible and keep an eye for additional communication regarding our new self-service password reset portal.
Thank You MSOE Alumni Email Team

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Sound not coming out of HDMI connected MondoPad. Below are the steps to set the default sound to the HDMI cable.
1) Click the Windows Button 2) In the search bar, Type 'Sound' 3) Open Sound 4) Under devices, you should see the HDMI cable. Right click it. 5) Select Set as Default Device
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

1) Click the Windows Button
2) In the search bar, Type 'Sound'
3) Open Sound
4) Under devices, you should see the HDMI cable. Right click it.
5) Select Set as Default Device

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Leander,
One way to accomplish this is to use the "View & Share" capabilities of the MondoPad. By pressing the icon, you will be given a screen that allows you to view the screen via browser. It will give you an address to type in. Simply type the address into the second MondoPad's browser, and you will be sharing the same screen between the two.
Notes: *Only the original will be able to actually interact with the program. The second MondoPad will simply display the screen of the first. **You must be in the MondoPad program to do this. Closing the MondoPad and using Windows doesn't have the same functionality. We can certainly explore other screen sharing apps if this is desired.

One way to accomplish this is to use the "View & Share" capabilities of the MondoPad.  By pressing the icon, you will be given a screen that allows you to view the screen via browser.  It will give you an address to type in.  Simply type the address into the second MondoPad's browser, and you will be sharing the same screen between the two.

Notes:
*Only the original will be able to actually interact with the program.  The second MondoPad will simply display the screen of the first.
**You must be in the MondoPad program to do this.  Closing the MondoPad and using Windows doesn't have the same functionality.  We can certainly explore other screen sharing apps if this is desired.

helpdesk-note.body: I could not find the setup info, forwarding to AV
helpdesk-note.body-html: I could not find the setup info, forwarding to AV

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Quin Krisik,
This is simply a display monitor. There are VGA and HDMI cables connected to the monitor. Simply attach the cables and press the input button on the side of the monitor for the correct display type. Unfortunately, there are no touch-screen capabilities on this display. In addition, sometimes you need to change the output on the PC to "Duplicate" or "Extended Screen" mode. On a Windows PC, this can be easily done by pressing "Windows + P."
I hope this helps.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Positive Pay Errors
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
Beth suggested that we fill out a ticket for this.
We have a nightly job in Jenzbar that is pulling data on checks written for us to upload to our bank’s fraud controls. It is critical that the information in the file match the data printed on the check or we will be charged by the bank and the cash will not clear.
Here’s how the check we submitted to the bank looked on the file from Jenzabar: C028000001229486 RA 0000389670000007952304111600000000000000303829Trane
This was paid to vendor #303829 who’s name only shows up as Trane U.S. Inc. in our records (printed on the check and on their vendor card).
Thank you for your help! Jo
Jo Smith Controller Milwaukee School of Engineering (414)277-2249 www.msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: Hello Kimberly Benson, The power cord, for some reason, was only connected to the speakers underneath the screen. Jordan Hendrickson

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Re: [#INC-7377] Display in Nursing Lounge Setup
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Thank you that helps so much!
Quin Krisik
On Apr 21, 2016, at 10:38 AM, helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>> wrote:
Hi Quin Krisik,
This is simply a display monitor. There are VGA and HDMI cables connected to the monitor. Simply attach the cables and press the input button on the side of the monitor for the correct display type. Unfortunately, there are no touch-screen capabilities on this display. In addition, sometimes you need to change the output on the PC to "Duplicate" or "Extended Screen" mode. On a Windows PC, this can be easily done by pressing "Windows + P."
I hope this helps.
Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed Instructional Technology Technician Office: CC307 email: holmes@msoe.edu<mailto:holmes@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Hasker,
Right now, the guest network has the same access as the wired network, and as authenticated MSOE wireless. This was an ease-of-use premise that wasn't necessarily in line with security best practices. With a new senior director with a more technical background, we're looking at ways to shore up some of the holes in the way IT has done things in the past.
This will probably mean that the guest network will only have internet access, and at a very limited speed. The details haven't been fully realized yet, the policies we want to base these changes off have yet to be written, and we want to have a full understanding of how it will impact users before we do anything.
I'll keep you posted, but I don't see any of these changes being made without policies and procedures in place first.

Hi IT,
Can you please tell me what the problem was? How did you resolve it that you’re comfortable closing this ticket? I promise you I did not ask for 9 copies instead of 3 so I would really like to know how to avoid this in the future.
FYI: I would always like to know how to fix an error so I don’t make it again instead of a blanket email that tells me nothing of what was done, who worked on it, or how to avoid future problems.
If I try to print multiple copies of a color document and it still triples my request, that is going to upset me, because your reply here is telling me it won’t happen again because it has been resolved.
From a user/customer standpoint, it would be better that a ticket stay active until an answer is found than to close it out each time without fixing the root cause and making users keep entering tickets for the exact same issue.
I truly think if you include some of this sort of information in your replies to the MSOE community, you will find your ratings will improve.
Thank you very much for your efforts on our behalf.
Sarah Rowell

helpdesk-note.body: I was unable to check the room due to a meeting. Im thinking this might have something to do with the occupancy sensor in the room.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I was unable to check the room due to a meeting. Im thinking this might have something to do with the occupancy sensor in the room.

helpdesk-note.body: Occupancy sensor should only work with the lights. There must be a timer on the system/projector that needs to be adjusted. Otherwise, perhaps the lamp or fan is causing the projector to auto-shutdown. Whoever is working Friday should check this out - and clean the filter while you are there as that also could be an issue.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Occupancy sensor should only work with the lights.  There must be a timer on the system/projector that needs to be adjusted.  Otherwise, perhaps the lamp or fan is causing the projector to auto-shutdown.  Whoever is working Friday should check this out - and clean the filter while you are there as that also could be an issue.

helpdesk-note.body: I checked out the system today, and made a few changes. I cleaned the air filter and went into the settings for the system and changed the standby timeout from 10 min to 90 min. Hopefully these changes will solve the issue.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I checked out the system today, and made a few changes. I cleaned the air filter and went into the settings for the system and changed the standby timeout from 10 min to 90 min. Hopefully these changes will solve the issue.
